    <field name="scopecontent_teim">This recording is similar to that on MC.259.cuid5128.  Landy introduces the lecture on Everett L. Shostrom's 1965 Three Approaches to Psychotherapy and his work to create a modern version of this for drama therapy.  Landy demonstrates role method and role theory, David Reed Johnson demonstrates developmental transformations, and Nina Garcia demonstrates psychodrama.  The recording ends with a performance by students acting out dialogue of the patient in the three methods.</field>
